description: Generate atomic conventional commit messages from repo changes
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---

Use `RULES.md` in this repository as the single source of truth for commit message generation.

When the user asks for help generating, refining, or splitting a `git commit message`:

- Read and follow `RULES.md`
- Prefer staged changes over unstaged changes
- Output directly usable commit messages
- Do not run `git commit` automatically
